The paper discusses a model of human decision-making in task interleaving, which involves learning to switch between tasks based on task-specific utility estimates. This suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI), as well as human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning, which is a common topic in cybersecurity (cs.CYBER).
